        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="iIwD6QwnB8rfQwbx0LGv-1" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=18;" value="&lt;p&gt;Given:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;[&lt;br&gt;\frac{dy}{dx}=3x^2&lt;br&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This derivative tells us the &lt;strong&gt;slope of the function at any value of (x)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;To find the slope at (x=2), substitute (2) in place of (x):&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;[&lt;br&gt;\frac{dy}{dx}=3(2)^2&lt;br&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First calculate the square:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;[&lt;br&gt;2^2=2\times2=4&lt;br&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Then multiply by 3:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;[&lt;br&gt;3\times4=12&lt;br&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Therefore:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;[&lt;br&gt;\boxed{\frac{dy}{dx}=12 \text{ at } x=2}&lt;br&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For example, if the original function is:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;[&lt;br&gt;y=x^3&lt;br&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;then:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;[&lt;br&gt;\frac{dy}{dx}=3x^2&lt;br&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At (x=2), the curve has a slope of &lt;strong&gt;12&lt;/strong&gt;, meaning (y) is increasing by approximately 12 units for every small 1-unit increase in (x) near (x=2).&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="670" width="560" x="160" y="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="iIwD6QwnB8rfQwbx0LGv-2" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=22;" value="Large amount of training data&#xa; ↓&#xa;AI model learns patterns &#xa; ↓&#xa;User provides a prompt            ↓Model understands the request &#xa; ↓Model predicts and generates new content &#xa; ↓&#xa;User receives the output" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="240" width="560" x="50" y="1270" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
